# =====================================================================
# ServiYa — Suite de pruebas de notificaciones (RF-061 a RF-089)
# REST Client (VS Code extension: "REST Client" by Huachao Mao)
#
# Uso secuencial:
#   1. Ejecuta cada bloque en orden (las flechas verdes "Send Request").
#   2. Las variables (@xxx) se capturan automáticamente de respuestas previas.
#   3. Entre cada escenario, verifica en frontend que llegó la notificación.
#
# Usuarios:
#   Cliente : jbeltrano@unal.edu.co / asdfasdf
#   Oferente: juanpdnejoh@gmail.com / asdfasdf
#   Servicio: 5
# =====================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

# =====================================================================
# 1. LOGIN — captura tokens de ambos usuarios
# =====================================================================

### 1a. Login Cliente
# @name loginClient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jbeltrano@unal.edu.co",
  "password": "asdfasdf"
}

@clientToken = {{loginClient.response.body.token}}
@clientId = {{loginClient.response.body.id}}

### 1b. Login Oferente
# @name loginOfferer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juanpdnejoh@gmail.com",
  "password": "asdfasdf"
}

@offererToken = {{loginOfferer.response.body.token}}
@offererId = {{loginOfferer.response.body.id}}

# =====================================================================
# 2. DIRECCIÓN del cliente (si no existe, créala; si ya existe, omite)
# =====================================================================

### 2a. Crear dirección (solo si no tiene ninguna)
# @name createAddress
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/addresses
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "addressLine": "Carrera 45 # 12-34",
  "city": "Bogotá",
  "latitude": 4.60971,
  "longitude": -74.08175
}

@addressId = {{createAddress.response.body.id}}

# =====================================================================
# 3. CONSULTAS INICIALES — verificar estado antes de empezar
# =====================================================================

### 3a. Ver notificaciones del cliente (debe estar vacío/viejo)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=ALL
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### 3b. Ver notificaciones del oferente (debe estar vacío/viejo)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=ALL
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO A — RF-061: Cliente crea solicitud → notifica oferente
#                RF-062: Oferente acepta → notifica cliente
# Estado final: solicitud ACCEPTED
# =====================================================================

### A1. Cliente crea solicitud #101
# @name createReq101
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-07-10T09:00:00"
}

@req101Id = {{createReq101.response.body.id}}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "Nueva solicitud de servicio"
### A2. Oferente acepta solicitud #101
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req101Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: cliente recibió notificación "Tu solicitud fue aceptada"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO B — RF-085: Oferente rechaza → notifica cliente
# Estado final: solicitud REJECTED
# =====================================================================

### B1. Cliente crea solicitud #102
# @name createReq102
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-07-10T10:00:00"
}

@req102Id = {{createReq102.response.body.id}}

### B2. Oferente rechaza solicitud #102
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req102Id}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: cliente recibió notificación "Tu solicitud fue rechazada por ..."

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO C — RF-089: Oferente declara completado → notifica cliente
#                RF-088: Cliente confirma → notifica oferente
# Estado final: solicitud COMPLETED
# =====================================================================

### C1. Cliente crea solicitud #103
# @name createReq103
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-07-10T10:00:00"
}

@req103Id = {{createReq103.response.body.id}}

### C2. Oferente acepta solicitud #103
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req103Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### C3. Oferente marca #103 como presumiblemente completada
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req103Id}}/mark-completed
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: cliente recibió notificación "... declaró el servicio como realizado"
### C4. Cliente confirma completitud de #103
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req103Id}}/confirm-completion
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "... confirmó que el servicio fue completado"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO D — RF-086: Cliente cancela → notifica oferente
# Estado final: solicitud CANCELLED
# =====================================================================

### D1. Cliente crea solicitud #104
# @name createReq104
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-08-04T12:00:00"
}

@req104Id = {{createReq104.response.body.id}}

### D2. Cliente cancela solicitud #104
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req104Id}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "cancelada por el Cliente"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO E — RF-087: Cliente reprograma → notifica oferente
# Estado final: solicitud original RESCHEDULED + reemplazo ACCEPTED
# =====================================================================

### E1. Cliente crea solicitud #105
# @name createReq105
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-08-05T13:00:00"
}

@req105Id = {{createReq105.response.body.id}}

### E2. Oferente acepta solicitud #105
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req105Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### E3. Cliente reprograma #105 a nueva fecha
# @name reschedule105
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req105Id}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newDate": "2026-08-20T09:00:00"
}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "... reprogramó el servicio"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO F — Propuesta reprogramación: crear → aceptar
#                (notifica cliente → notifica oferente)
# =====================================================================

### F1. Cliente crea solicitud #106
# @name createReq106
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-08-06T14:00:00"
}

@req106Id = {{createReq106.response.body.id}}

### F2. Oferente acepta solicitud #106
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req106Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### F3. Oferente crea propuesta de reprogramación para #106
# @name createPropF
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestId": {{req106Id}},
  "reason": "Inconveniente de agenda",
  "proposedDate": "2026-08-25T10:00:00"
}

@propFId = {{createPropF.response.body.id}}

### → VERIFICAR: cliente recibió notificación "... propuso reprogramar"
### F4. Cliente acepta propuesta #{{propFId}}
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals/{{propFId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "... aceptó la propuesta"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO G — Propuesta reprogramación: rechazar
#                (notifica cliente → notifica oferente)
# =====================================================================

### G1. Cliente crea solicitud #107
# @name createReq107
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-08-07T15:00:00"
}

@req107Id = {{createReq107.response.body.id}}

### G2. Oferente acepta solicitud #107
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req107Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### G3. Oferente crea propuesta de reprogramación para #107
# @name createPropG
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestId": {{req107Id}},
  "reason": "Necesito cambiar la fecha",
  "proposedDate": "2026-08-26T10:00:00"
}

@propGId = {{createPropG.response.body.id}}

### G4. Cliente rechaza propuesta #{{propGId}}
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals/{{propGId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: oferente recibió notificación "... rechazó la propuesta"

# =====================================================================
# ESCENARIO H — Propuesta reprogramación: oferente retira
#                (notifica cliente → notifica oferente)
# =====================================================================

### H1. Cliente crea solicitud #108
# @name createReq108
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 5,
  "addressId": {{addressId}},
  "scheduledDate": "2026-08-10T16:00:00"
}

@req108Id = {{createReq108.response.body.id}}

### H2. Oferente acepta solicitud #108
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service-requests/{{req108Id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### H3. Oferente crea propuesta de reprogramación para #108
# @name createPropH
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestId": {{req108Id}},
  "reason": "Propuesta por error",
  "proposedDate": "2026-08-27T10:00:00"
}

@propHId = {{createPropH.response.body.id}}

### H4. Oferente retira (cancela) propuesta #{{propHId}}
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reschedule-proposals/{{propHId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### → VERIFICAR: cliente recibió notificación "... retiró la propuesta"

# =====================================================================
# 4. VERIFICACIONES FINALES — listar notificaciones recibidas
# =====================================================================

### 4a. Notificaciones del cliente (debería ver ~8 no leídas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=ALL
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### 4b. Notificaciones del oferente (debería ver ~8 no leídas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=ALL
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### 4c. Solo no leídas del cliente
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=UNREAD
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### 4d. Solo no leídas del oferente
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications?page=0&size=20&filter=UNREAD
Authorization: Bearer {{offererToken}}

### 4e. Marcar primera notificación del cliente como leída (reemplazar {deliveryId})
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications/1/read
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### 4f. Marcar todas como leídas (cliente) — si existe endpoint
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications/read-all
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

# =====================================================================
# 5. MAPA DE NOTIFICACIONES ESPERADAS
# =====================================================================
#
# Cliente recibe (5 notificaciones):
#   A2 → "aceptada por [nombre]"                         (request_accepted)
#   B2 → "rechazada por [nombre]"                        (request_rejected)
#   C3 → "[nombre] declaró el servicio como realizado"   (service_completed)
#   F3 → "[nombre] propuso reprogramar para [fecha]"     (reschedule_proposed)
#   H4 → "[nombre] retiró la propuesta"                  (reschedule_cancelled)
#
# Oferente recibe (~13 notificaciones):
#   A1/B1/C1/D1/E1/F1/G1/H1 → 8 × "Nueva solicitud"     (new_request)
#   C4 → "confirmó que el servicio fue completado"        (completion_confirmed)
#   D2 → "cancelada por el Cliente"                      (request_cancelled)
#   E3 → "[cliente] reprogramó para [fecha]"             (request_rescheduled)
#   F4 → "[cliente] aceptó la propuesta"                 (reschedule_accepted)
#   G4 → "[cliente] rechazó la propuesta"                (reschedule_rejected)
#
# =====================================================================
